lost_doc_db


Click Create

Create tables for Found Documents (your friend focuses on found table):

CREATE TABLE found_documents (
  id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
  name VARCHAR(100),
  doc_type VARCHAR(50),
  doc_number VARCHAR(50),
  contact VARCHAR(100),
  description TEXT,
  date TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
);


(Optional: also create lost_documents table if needed for search later, but focus on found_documents today)

ðŸªœ Step 4: Create Database Connection File

Inside includes/, create:

db_connect.php


Open and paste:

<?php
$servername = "localhost";
$username = "root";
$password = "";
$database = "lost_doc_db";

$conn = new mysqli($servername, $username, $password, $database);

if ($conn->connect_error) {
    die("Connection failed: " . $conn->connect_error);
}
?>


âœ… This will allow all PHP pages to connect to the database.

